      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAYNE CARGO (4) is better than last start when eighth (17.98) in a Grade 4/5 at Taree Super Track over 300m. Solid winning record at this trip. Got the money at his only try from this box. Ready to return to form. MAYBE YES (8) led all the way last time out to score by 1.75 lengths (19.56) at this track in a Grade 5 over 340m. Comes through a solid form race last start. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. TIPSY ETHICS (1) struggled in tougher grade last start after missing the jump at this track, but prior to that won easily by 4.5 lengths at this track (19.64) beating KATIE KEEPING in a Grade 5 on April 8. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Has ability and is one of the better chances. KATIE KEEPING (2) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.",
